
<% if current_user %>


<div class="dm-right-corner"></div>
<div class="container">
<div class="row">
<div class="col-md-7 ">
<div class="dm-banner-title">
    <div class="front-text-box">
        <h1>Welcome  <%= current_user.username %></h1>
    </div>
<div class="back-box"></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="col-md-12 ">
    <h1 style="font-size:25px; padding:1px  "><%= link_to "Log Out", destroy_user_session_path, method: :delete%></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="box">
<div class="container">
<div class="row">
<div class="col-lg-4 col-md-4 col-sm-4 col-xs-12">
<div class="box-part text-center">
    <div class="title">
        <h4>Authentication of user</h4>
    </div>
    <div class="text">
        <span>Users are prompted to log in and create an account. A user password token is only accessible through command line.</span>
    </div>
    </div>
</div>	 

<div class="col-lg-4 col-md-4 col-sm-4 col-xs-12">
<div class="box-part text-center">
    <div class="title">
        <h4>Organisations</h4>
    </div>
    <div class="text">
        <span>Users have the ability to join an organisation, leave an organisation, edit an organisation and view shifts related to that organisation. A limation is that when a user doesn't belong to an organisation this user isn't informed on main page.</span>
    </div>
    </div>
</div>	 

<div class="col-lg-4 col-md-4 col-sm-4 col-xs-12">
<div class="box-part text-center">
    <div class="title">
        <h4>Shifts</h4>
    </div>
    <div class="text">
        <span>Breaks are unpaid and subtracted off shift length to determine hours works. Users have the ability to add shifts, delete shifts and edit shifts. A limitation is the hours worked are not formatted to be as readable as it should be.</span>
    </div>
    </div>
</div>	 

<div class="col-lg-4 col-md-4 col-sm-4 col-xs-12">

<div class="box-part text-center">
    <div class="title">
        <h4>Optional Features</h4>
    </div>
    <div class="text">
        <span>Users can modify and delete existing shifts. </span>
    </div>
    </div>
</div>	 
				
